					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Hi all. I just bought what I thought was a cheap USB chip programmer off eBay. It's not (I'll be giving it away soon). Anyway, I am looking for suggestions for a good chip programmer that supports a wide range of memory and MCU's. My budget is $100 to $150. Any suggestions? It needs to be 100% USB (or USB + AC/DC Power). I'd like it to support ATtiny and ATmega series MCU's as well.
<br />
<br />Thanks!</div>

